;There are two categories of data that we collect by default in our release version of Firefox.
Il ha duo categorias de datos que nos collige per option predefinite in nostre version de edition de Firefox.


;The first is what we call "technical data." This is data about the browser itself, such as the operating system it is running on and information about errors or crashes.
Le prime es illos que nos appella "datos technic. "Istos es datos circa le navigator ipse, tal como le systema operative sur que es fluente, e le informationes circa errores o crashes.


;The second is what we call "interaction data." This is data about an individual's engagement with Firefox, such as the number of tabs that were open, the status of user preferences, or number of times certain browser features were used, such as screenshots or containers. For example, we collect this data in terms of the back button, that arrow in the upper left corner of your browser that lets you navigate back to a previous webpage in a way that shows us someone used the back button, but doesn’t tell what specific webpages are accessed.
Le secunde es illos que nos appella "datos de interaction." Istos es datos circa un comenciamento de un persona con Firefox, tal como le numero del schedas que esseva aperte, le stato del preferentias del usator, o le numero de vices que certe functionalitates del navigator esseva usate, tal como instantaneos de schermo o receptaculos. Pro exemplo, nos collige iste datos in terminos del button Receder, ille flecha in le angulo superior sinistre de tu navigator que te lassa navigar retro pro un previe pagina web, in maniera que monstras nos si alcuno ha usate le button Receder, ma non dice nos que paginas web specific es accedite.


;Do you collect more data in pre-release versions of Firefox?
